    "(40) that depends on the black hole mass, luminosity and accretion efficiency, or be purely phenomenological (for example Eq.",
    "We can collectively denote all the free parameters of the source as η s.",
    "Simulated microlensing flux ratios as a function of wavelength are in fact a function of these free model parameters:",
    "To obtain the microlensing flux ratio in any photometric band one should in principle integrate over a range of wavelengths and take into account the band's response function.",
    "In practice, only the central wavelength of the band can be considered and the dependence on λ rest can be replaced by the index k. Finally, to obtain the ratios between images A and B we randomly select locations on the convolved maps and divide their magnification values pairwise."
